The paper discusses a new approach to solving constraint problems in a distributed manner by modifying the constraint model of the problem. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as constraint satisfaction problems are a common topic in AI research. The paper also discusses the distribution of computations across multiple machines, which falls under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of search trees and partitioning of search spaces, which are topics in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the ability to stop and restart computations and solve problems on machines that cannot communicate with each other, which falls under Software Engineering (cs.SE).
